# Claude task → Cursor validation

When Claude writes `docs/workflow/claude_task_result.json` for **T-001** (e.g. `task_id` starts with `T-001-`) with `"status": "ready_for_cursor_validation"`, run:

```bash
.venv/bin/python tools/cursor_validation_gate.py
```

- **Do not bypass the gate** (no manual `git commit` of the same changes without running the tool).
- **Commit only if validation passes** (use `--no-commit` only when you intentionally need validation without a commit).

The tool runs `required_validation` in `.venv` (loads `.env` when present), gatekeeps the working tree against `files_changed` / `docs_to_update` / `docs/workflow/`, writes `docs/workflow/cursor_validation_result.json`, and commits using `commit_message` only when checks pass. Add `--include-optional` only when the task requires optional validations.

Other tasks: same procedure; match `task_id` / title in the JSON.
